A route documented by Tithe certifications has stronger continuity-of-use evidence than a route without documentation, even if the Tithe certification predates the charter system.
This has produced several legal disputes where surviving Tithe documentation supports property claims that post-charter documentation does not.
The Continuity faction treats Tithe documentation as the strongest available historical evidence for pre-charter route rights.
