Both factions agree that distinguishing legitimate from contested Tithe documentation requires case-by-case analysis. Neither faction agrees on who should conduct that analysis.
Midgaard's position: the Tithe was a valid legal regime for its period. Its documents have evidentiary value. Their weight requires individual assessment.

